@Comment:	Time is 14:07. side B
@Comment:	The mood is comfortable for this activity. EXP and EX2 remain in the background and do not participate in the discussion between Mot and Chi. Mot does the vast majority of the talking; Chi's longest utterance is about six words and most of his utterances are one to three word answers to questions which were posed by Mot. Mot spends a good deal of time talking to Chi about the scientific ideas behind magnetism , reminding him that they had read something about it previously. Unfortunately , MOT doesn't remember the general idea , that opposites attract and like poles repel , and it's hard to tell if Chi knows this since he doesn't verbalize it clearly. The final part of the activity is spent building a structure
